The course continues the preparation of students for teaching English on the two first schools tages. The topics include: teaching grammar and pronunciation, integrating English with other subjects, project work, testing, error correction, using songs and technology in lessons, etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To continue providing students with didactic skills for teaching English on the first two school stages.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student: - knows and uses the terminology of ELT methodology as well as the theoretical principles related to the topics discussed; - knows and can use methodological techniques, including those related to using digital technology, for teaching English at primary level within the range of topics discussed; - has an overview of the main principles and techniques of foreign language teaching methods; - designs a test and an assessment scale for primary school students in order to assess their English knowledge and skills; - designs an activity that is based on project work, digital technology and/or integration between subjects for teaching English at the primary level; - analyses their own as well as fellow-students' homework.
